theorem Topology.dense_interior_iff_interior_closure_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior A) ↔ interior (closure (interior A)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hDense
    have hClosure : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
    simpa [hClosure] using
      (interior_univ : interior (Set.univ : Set X) = Set.univ)
  · intro hInt
    have hClosure : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      apply subset_antisymm
      · intro x _hx; trivial
      · intro x hx
        have hx_int : x ∈ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
          simpa [hInt] using hx
        exact
          (interior_subset :
              interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (interior A)) hx_int
    simpa [Dense] using hClosure

theorem Topology.closed_dense_eq_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hClosed : IsClosed A) (hDense : Dense A) :
    A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  -- Since `A` is closed, its closure is itself.
  have h₁ : closure A = A := hClosed.closure_eq
  -- Since `A` is dense, its closure is the whole space.
  have h₂ : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
  -- Combining the two equalities yields the desired result.
  simpa [h₁] using h₂
